      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "In some localities up to 50 cm of snow fell on Sunday above approximately 2000 m. The fresh snow and the sometimes deep wind slabs are bonding only slowly with the old snowpack. The sleet gave rise to moistening of the snowpack below approximately 1800 m. <br/> Distinct weak layers in the old snowpack are treacherous. Especially above approximately 2000 m northwest, north and northeast facing slopes:"
